explanations.reason: The paper focuses on the responsiveness of out-of-pocket healthcare spending to macroeconomic factors and different health financing schemes using fixed-random effects and dynamic panel data methodology. It does not mention any machine learning techniques, algorithms, or models such as supervised learning, unsupervised learning, neural networks, or any other related keywords. The study is purely based on econometric analysis and does not involve any of the listed machine learning or deep learning concepts.
